    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCreery</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Valparaiso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The president, managing director, and one other director of the South American
                    Steamship Company declare before me that the steamer <hi rend="italic"
                        >Itata</hi> is the property of said company, and that she was taken by force
                    and is now in the service of the revolutionary party without the consent of the
                    company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. B. McCreery</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States Consul</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
